# 2. Code Implementation

Changes made to the Django application to implement server-side OpenID Connect SSO using MSAL.

| **#** | **Component** | **What Was Done** | **File** | **Status** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | sso.py module | Built MSAL confidential client with build_auth_flow() and redeem_code() functions | /app/optimizer/sso.py | Completed |
| 2 | sso_login view | Initiates OAuth auth-code flow — stores MSAL flow in DB session and redirects to Microsoft login | /app/optimizer/views.py | Completed |
| 3 | sso_callback view | Handles Entra redirect — validates state/PKCE/nonce, redeems code, provisions Editor user, signs in | /app/optimizer/views.py | Completed |
| 4 | URL routes | Registered /auth/sso/login/ and /auth/sso/callback/ URL patterns | /app/optimizer/urls.py | Completed |
| 5 | Django SSO settings | Added SSO_TENANT_ID, SSO_CLIENT_ID, SSO_CLIENT_SECRET, SSO_AUTHORITY, SSO_SCOPES, SSO_REDIRECT_URI, SSO_ENABLED | /app/sql_license_optimizer/settings.py | Completed |
| 6 | Session in PostgreSQL | SESSION_ENGINE = db so auth flow state is shared across all container replicas | /app/sql_license_optimizer/settings.py | Completed |
| 7 | SSO_REDIRECT_URI = Front Door URL | Explicit public callback URL used so Django builds the correct redirect URI behind Front Door | /app/sql_license_optimizer/settings.py | Completed |

