# 5. Azure Portal — WAF Configuration Steps

Step-by-step actions taken in Azure Portal to resolve WAF blocking of the SSO callback.

| **Step#** | **Action** | **Where in Portal** | **Outcome** | **Status** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Located Front Door profile | Azure Portal → rg-ac-license-agreement-171817-sandbox → afd-mvp6-9280-sandbox | Confirmed Front Door profile name | Completed |
| 2 | Checked Security policies | afd-mvp6-9280-sandbox → Security → Security policies | Found 1 policy: secpol-mvp6-9280-sandbox linked to WAF wafmvp69280sandbox | Completed |
| 3 | Added custom Allow rule (AllowSSO) | wafmvp69280sandbox → Custom rules → + Add Priority: 1 │ Match variable: Request URI │ Operator: Begins with │ Value: /auth/sso/callback/ │ Action: Allow traffic | Rule created — but SSO still blocked (Bot Protection was the real cause) | Completed |
| 4 | Switched WAF to Detection mode | wafmvp69280sandbox → Overview → Switch to detection mode | Confirmed SSO still blocked — root cause was NOT main WAF ruleset | Completed |
| 5 | Checked Managed rules | wafmvp69280sandbox → Managed rules → Managed Rulesets | Found BotProtection_preview-0.1 → Bot00001 (Malicious Bots) still set to Block independently | Completed |
| 6 | Changed Bot00001 action to Log | wafmvp69280sandbox → Managed rules → select Bot00001 → Change action → Log | Stops Bot Protection from blocking SSO callback | Completed |
| 7 | Enabled WAF diagnostic logs | afd-mvp6-9280-sandbox → Diagnostic settings → + Add diagnostic setting Log: FrontDoorWebApplicationFirewallLog → log-mvp6-9280-sandbox workspace | WAF block logs now flow to Log Analytics for troubleshooting | Completed |

